Important Points from Week 1



Characteristics of Database : Persistency, Inter-related, Shared.
Apart from the data, two important things in a database are Entities and Reltionships.
Data administrator has more planning responsibilities than database administrator.
Central repositories in data warehouse usually can be populated from Operational database and external sources.


C:\Program Files\Oracle\VirtualBox ... destination folder for Oracle VM

Week 2
To make use of relational databases, we use matching values.
The equivalent set-oriented terminologies for the table-oriented terminologies for Table, Row and Column are : 
      Relation, Tuple and Attribute.
     
Entity integrity means: Rows cannot share the same primary key values.
